<HEADLINE> Frito-Lay Exec Leading Tropicana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRADENTON, Fla. (AP) -- PepsiCo Inc. has named Brock Leach as the  
new president and chief executive officer of Tropicana Products 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Leach, 40, has spent the last 17 years at Frito-Lay -- another  
division of No. 2 soft-drink maker PepsiCo. He replaces Gary 
Rodkin, who was picked last week to head Pepsi-Cola North America. 
</P>
<P>
	Leach said his greatest challenge at Tropicana will be  
continuing the innovations begun by Rodkin and his team of 
managers. Tropicana is developing new products and versions of 
existing products through a $17 million technology and research 
center at the juice company's Bradenton headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
	Most recently, Leach was president of Frito-Lay Development Co.  
He helped Frito-Lay revamp Doritos Tortilla Chips, launch Baked 
Lay's and Baked Tostitos, and introduce the WOW! snack line made 
with the fat substitute Olean, and sold under the Lay's, Ruffles 
and Doritos names. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
