<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Abandon Ship as Tug Sinks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Eight people abandoned ship today as a  
tugboat began sinking about 350 miles northeast of Jacksonville in 
tropical storm force winds whipped up by Hurricane Floyd, Coast 
Guard officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	The USS Kennedy, an aircraft carrier based in Jacksonville,  
launched helicopters to attempt to locate the crew members who took 
to a lifeboat. 
</P>
<P>
	It was not clear whether winds and rough seas from the hurricane  
were directly responsible for the tugboat taking on water. 
</P>
<P>
	``Floyd did not help the situation,'' Coast Guard Chief Petty  
Officer John Ware said in Miami. The tugboat crew contacted its 
office, and office staffers then called the Coast Guard. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
