<HEADLINE> AP Names Missouri Correspondent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Doug Johnson, a newsman in the Albany,  
N.Y., bureau of The Associated Press, has been named correspondent 
in Springfield. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Wednesday by Paul Stevens, chief  
of bureau for Missouri and Kansas. Johnson succeeds John Rogers, 
who moved to the AP's Los Angeles bureau as night supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, 25, is a graduate of the University of New Mexico. He  
joined the AP in Albuquerque in 1997 and moved to Albany a year 
later. 
</P>
