<HEADLINE> Colts Release Defensive Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- The Indianapolis Colts released defensive  
back Monty Montgomery and signed running back Tremayne Stephens to 
take his spot on the active roster Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Montgomery was in his third year with the Colts and started  
eight games in 33 games. The 5-foot-11, 197-pounder was used on 
special teams in the Colts' 31-14 over Buffalo last week. A 
fourth-round draft pick out of Houston in 1997, Montgomery had 
played in all 32 games the previous two seasons. He had 76 tackles, 
including 64 solo, and recorded three sacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Stephens was originally signed as a free agent by San Diego last  
year and was waived Monday. The 5-11, 213-pound Stephens played 13 
games for the Chargers last year with one start. Stephens had 122 
yards rushing last year and averaged nearly 22 yards per kickoff 
return. 
  	   	
</P>
