<HEADLINE> GPU Energy Head Leaving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MORRISTOWN, N.J. (AP) -- Dennis P. Baldassari will resign as  
president and chief operating officer of GPU Energy, which operates 
utilities that serve 2 million electricity customers in New Jersey 
and Pennsylvania, the company's parent announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Baldassari, 50, is leaving the $3.4 billion unit at the end of  
the month ``to pursue other interests,'' said Morristown-based GPU 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	He did not immediately respond to a request for an interview  
that was made through company spokesman Jeff Dennard. 
</P>
<P>
	Baldassari joined GPU in 1968 and has been president of GPU  
Energy, of Reading, Pa., since it was created in 1996 by the 
combination of GPU's three utilities, Jersey Central Power &AMP; Light 
Co., Metropolitan Edison Co. and Pennsylvania Electric Co. 
</P>
<P>
	GPU said a search for a successor has begun. In the interim, the  
presidency will be assumed by Robert L. Wise, president of GPU's 
generation and independent power subsidiaries, the company said. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
