<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Rallies at Champions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Seven-time champion Real Madrid scored with 10 minutes left,  
sending the Spanish club to a 3-3 tie with Olympiakos on Wednesday 
in the Champions Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Raul Gonzalez had the key goal for Real Madrid in Athens in one  
of eight first-round, first-leg games in tournament play. 
</P>
<P>
	Zatko Zahovic had put Olympiakos up 3-2 in the 67th minute.  
Giovanni scored the other two goals for the Greek champions. Savio 
and Roberto Carlos also scored for Real. 
</P>
<P>
