3-1 win at Willem II while Sparta Prague and Bordeaux played a 
scoreless tie in the other Group G game. 
</P>
<P>
	Beaten by Manchester United in last season's final, Bayern  
Munich edged PSV Eindhoven 2-1 with two goals from Brazilian Paolo 
Sergio. 
</P>
<P>
	Valencia went to the top of Group F with a 2-0 win over Glasgow  
Rangers, helped by an own-goal by Scottish champion defender Craig 
Moore. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, defending champion Manchester United was held to a  
0-0 at home by Croatia Zagreb, and Olympique Marseille went to the 
top of Group D by downing Sturm Graz 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Romania's Maribor, expected to be the weakest team in Group A,  
went to the top after a 1-0 upset victory at Dynamo Kiev, a 
semifinalist last year. Bayer Leverkusen and Lazio tied 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
	Barcelona scored two goals in the last four minutes to win 2-1  
at Sweden's AIK to lead Group B while Fiorentina and Arsenal tied 
0-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Norway's Rosenborg won 3-0 at Portugal's Boavista to top Group C  
while Feyenoord and Borussia Dortmund tied 1-1. 
  	   	
</P>
