<HEADLINE> Bruce Lee Gallery Planned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HONG KONG (AP) -- In an attempt to boost tourism, Hong Kong plans  
to build a memorial gallery for the late Kung Fu star Bruce Lee and 
a Hollywood-style ``Walk of Fame.'' 
</P>
<P>
	City councilors have approved plans to set up a Bruce Lee  
Memorial Gallery as part of the Hong Kong Film Archive, a publicly 
funded library and museum for the city's world-renowned film 
industry. 
</P>
<P>
	The San Francisco-born Lee helped popularize Chinese martial  
arts in the West through a series of Kung Fu films before his 
sudden death in 1973 at the age of 33. 
</P>
<P>
	Separately, the Hong Kong Tourist Association announced it would  
build a Walk of Fame to honor its stars, many of whom have gained 
international recognition in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
	Lee, director John Woo, and Hollywood stars Jackie Chan, Chow  
Yun-fat and Sammo Hung are expected to be among those honored. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
