<HEADLINE> Canucks Re-Sign Scatchard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCOUVER, British Columbia (AP) -- The Vancouver Canucks  
re-signed free-agent center Dave Scatchard on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of Scatchard's contract weren't disclosed, but the signing  
comes five days after the Canucks issued the two-year veteran a 
take-it-or-leave-it final offer. 
</P>
<P>
	Scatchard, 23, was primarily a third- and fourth-line center  
last season, finishing with 13 goals and a career-high 26 points, 
along with 140 penalty minutes in 82 games. 
</P>
<P>
	With Scatchard under contract, the Canucks have yet to sign  
blue-liners Ed Jovanovski and Adrian Aucoin, whose 23 goals were a 
club record for a defenseman. 
</P>
<P>
	Assistant general manager Dave Nonis said he hasn't had any  
progress with the players this week. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully, we'll be able to close the gaps and get some deals  
done, but right now I can't tell you that we're close,'' said 
Nonis, adding that the sides are particularly far apart in 
negotiations with Aucoin. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
