<HEADLINE> Rob Reiner Honored for Politicism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Los Angeles County supervisors honored  
Director Rob Reiner for his accomplishments outside the film 
industry. 
</P>
<P>
	The supervisors on Tuesday cited Reiner for his work championing  
voter-approved Proposition 10, which increased the price of 
cigarettes by 50 cents a pack to raise money for youth programs. 
</P>
<P>
	Reiner said as a consequence, cigarette sales dropped 29 percent  
statewide in the first half of 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a lot of tobacco companies not very happy over the  
fact that we did pass this initiative,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Reiner directed ``When Harry Met Sally'' and ``A Few Good Men''  
and starred in the TV series ``All in the Family.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
