<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed; Dow Up 83.90 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks rose this morning after a tame  
inflation report help calm investors' fears that the Federal 
Reserve would raise interest rates for the third time this year. 
But technology shares lost ground, giving up some of Tuesday's 
sharp gains. 
</P>
<P>
	In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones  
industrial average was up 83.90 at 10,994.23, erasing much of 
Tuesday's 120-point loss. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500  
index was up 8.10 at 1,344.39, while the Nasdaq composite index was 
down 3.02 at 2,865.27, after climbing more than 23 points on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks rose today after the Labor Department reported that the  
August increase in its Consumer Price Index -- the most closely 
watched inflation gauge -- matched the 0.3 percent July advance. 
</P>
<P>
	Excluding the big gains in the gasoline and energy categories,  
prices rose a mere 0.1 percent in August, well below what Wall 
Street economists had expected. 
</P>
<P>
	That helped temper concerns that the Fed will need to boost  
interest rates for the third time this year as it tries to prevent 
inflation from escalating. 
</P>
<P>
	The report also helped lift prices in the inflation-sensitive  
bond market, which sent yields on 30-year Treasury bonds down to 
6.08 percent this morning from 6.12 percent late Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Inflation jitters were heightened Tuesday after the Commerce  
Department reported retail sales surged 1.2 percent in August, the 
biggest increase in six months and nearly twice what economists had 
anticipated. 
</P>
<P>
	That report added to worries the economy is overheating  
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 12-to-7 margin on  
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 110.39 million 
shares in the early going today, up from 86.86 million shares on 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Russell 2000 index was up 1.72 at 439.96.  
</P>
<P>
	In afternoon trading overseas, Germany's DAX index was down 0.9  
percent, Britain's FT-SE 100 was unchanged, and France's CAC-40 was 
up 0.6 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial markets in Japan were closed for a national holiday.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
