<HEADLINE> Richard Simmons Helps 800-Pound Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PATERSON, N.J. (AP) -- Diet guru Richard Simmons has offered  
financial help to an ill 800-pound man recently rescued from his 
home. 
</P>
<P>
	Firefighters on Sunday cut a 54-square-foot hole in an apartment  
house wall so they could free Steven DeProspo and take him to a 
hospital on the back of a flatbed truck. 
</P>
<P>
	DeProspo, 31, and his mother now face eviction from their  
apartment because of the damage. 
</P>
<P>
	Simmons, in New Jersey for a book signing Tuesday night, heard  
about the duo's plight and offered to lend a helping hand. 
</P>
<P>
	``If it's just a matter of having the place cleaned up, I'd be  
happy to pay to have the place made presentable, as long as the 
landlord agrees to continue to let them live there,'' Simmons said. 
</P>
<P>
	The landlord, Jon Mendelson, said he would consider any offer  
from Simmons. 
  	   	
