<HEADLINE> NET-tel Gets $210M in Financing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Telecommunications company NET-tel  
Communications Inc. said today it has arranged for $210 million in 
equity and debt financing to construct a 50-city Internet, data and 
voice network. 
</P>
<P>
	Nortel Networks Corp. will provide $150 million of the financing  
and Williams Communications Group Inc., $30 million, NET-tel said 
in a statement. Also, Allied Capital Corp. and Gold &AMP; Appel 
together will invest $30 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The privately held NET-tel, based in Washington, provides local,  
long distance and Internet service to small and mid-sized 
businesses in 22 markets, including New York, Chicago and Los 
Angeles. 



</P>
