<DOCNO> APW19990915.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 13:40:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Senators Rally For Farm Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Flanked by dozens of farmers from across the  
country, Democratic senators demanded that Congress pass emergency 
farm relief and overhaul the Freedom to Farm Act. 
</P>
<P>
	``This Congress cannot leave without acting on agriculture,''  
said Minority Leader Tom Daschle of South Dakota. ``We cannot 
afford to wait.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, the Senate passed $7.4 billion in emergency aid to  
help keep struggling farmers in business. But the legislation still 
has not made it out of a Senate-House conference committee. 
</P>
<P>
	One of the senators, Democrat Paul Wellstone of Minnesota, later  
went on the Senate floor and talked about the farm crisis for 
several hours, tying up business to focus attention on the issue. 
Spokesman Jim Farrell said Wellstone would continue to do so in 
coming weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	Daschle said that during a trip back home, a boy had told him he  
wanted to become a farmer but his father would not let him. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is more than just about price,'' Daschle said. ``This is  
about a way of life.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Farmers and children stood behind the senators, some holding  
signs that said, ``Save Our Family Farms.'' Julie Baker, who 
described herself as a Missouri farm wife, said, ``We have totally 
hit rock-bottom in the countryside right now.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Democrats blame the 1996 Freedom to Farm Act, which overhauled  
farm subsidy programs going back to the Great Depression. The 
federal government still subsidizes farmers, but no longer 
guarantees a minimum price for their crops. 
</P>
<P>
	``We need to get rid of the most noxious weed populating America  
-- it's called the Freedom to Farm Act,'' said Sen. Tom Harkin, 
D-Iowa. Harkin also called on Congress to pass legislation 
sponsored by Wellstone imposing a moratorium on agribusiness 
mergers and acquisitions. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
