<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-15 11:40:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Surgeon General, Fergie Team Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Surgeon General David Satcher teamed up with  
the Duchess of York on Wednesday to get the fat out. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's no question about the fact that obesity is at an  
all-time high in this country,'' Satcher said at a national 
conference on obesity. 
</P>
<P>
	About 55 percent of American adults -- 97 million people -- are  
considered overweight or obese. Doctors consider people obese if 
they weigh at least 20 percent more than what is recommended for 
their height. 
</P>
<P>
	``I know what it's like to be humiliated,'' said the former  
Sarah Ferguson, who once weighed 200 pounds and was dubbed 
``Duchess of Pork'' by the British tabloids. She is now a 
spokeswoman for Weight Watchers. 
</P>
<P>
	The former wife of Britain's Prince Andrew, looking thin in a  
cobalt-blue suit, said she keeps her weight down by sticking to a 
healthy diet and spending 20 minutes on a stationary bicycle every 
morning. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
