<HEADLINE> Terrell Davis Injures Right Wrist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Terrell Davis is unsure about his status for  
Sunday's game after he injured his right wrist in the Denver 
Broncos' 38-21 loss to Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	Davis' wrist was bandaged when he arrived at Mile High Stadium  
Tuesday to film a soup commercial. He also was nursing a scrape on 
his back from the Monday night game. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a physical game, but the game wasn't any more physical  
than games I've played in the past,'' said Davis, who gained 61 
yards on 19 carries. 
</P>
<P>
	The running back isn't sure when the wrist injury occurred.  
</P>
<P>
	``I just know that when I left the stadium, (the wrist) was  
stiff then,'' he said. ``When I woke up (Tuesday) morning, it was 
real stiff. I don't think it's broken or anything. But it's stiff, 
and it swelled up a bit.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Davis will be a spokesman for Campbell's Chunky Soup, and a  
Davis label will adorn cans of the soup. 
  	   	
